## How to get your Bearer Token

To access the DreamingSpanish API, we need to use your unique bearer token. This is a code that enables you (and this app) to acess the DreamingSpanish server and your stats.

:red-background[WARNING]: The bearer token allows full access to your account (but nothing too personal such as payment), so be careful where you paste it. It also contains your email and name. If you don't trust this app, there's always the option to run it locally and audit the code yourself ([available here](https://gitlab.com/b/dreaming-spanish-progress)). A bearer token is the **only** way to reliably access your stats at the moment since there is no official way to export your data or authenticate external apps.

### Firefox
1. Log into Dreaming Spanish
2. Open the Developer Tools (Ctrl+Shift+I)
3. Navigate to the "Storage" tab (you may need to use the dropdown)
4. Select the local storage section
5. Click the "token" field
6. Copy the token value (you may need to remove "token:" from the start and any quotation marks)
7. Paste it into the field at the top of the page and press "Go"

### Chrome

1. Log into Dreaming Spanish
2. Open the Developer Tools (Ctrl+Shift+I)
3. Navigate to the "Application" tab (you may need to use the dropdown)
4. Select the local storage section, then the Dreaming Spanish URL
5. Copy the token value from the token field
6. Paste it into the field at the top of the page and press "Go"
